    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-07-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="203"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/743.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-07-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that an American inspector of customs at Puerta Plata, while performing
                    his duties, was assaulted by a Dominican customs official; that he made
                    representations to the Dominican foreign office and demanded suspension from
                    office and punishment of this official and a guaranty for the future protection
                    of the receivership employees. He has been assured by the minister for foreign
                    affairs that proper measures have been taken; that the offender has been
                    suspended from duty and will be tried for the offense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
